{
  "stem": "15686.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we sewed it on his pajamas.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And it-- it was terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He punished us for weeks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Anyway, he tried to teach us that this was next to holy almost.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It turns out that later on, this has a great bearing on my story.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But my father could not understand that he, as a good German, who fought for the fatherland for four years and four of his brothers-- he was one of 10 children-- four of his brothers were also in the German army in World War I, both on the Russian front and the Western fronts, and the whole family had been very patriotic.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And he was highly decorated, and he could not understand that suddenly he was not considered German anymore.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He was just a Jew like any other Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And when we first heard stories of the Gestapo rounding up Jews and these Jews being taken to concentration camps, my father said pay no attention to that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "They're rounding up illegal Poles and Russian Jews that came to Germany, and they have no business here anyway.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And he was a bit of a snob, maybe a lot of-- more than a bit of a snob.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "He was a snob in that regard.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He looked down on Eastern European Jews, because German Jews were more cultured, and German Jews were more emancipated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "That was his favorite word.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And we were really Germans first, and he simply could not fathom that this right of being a German citizen was slowly being taken away from him.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would-- what did they do to us?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They would stop me on the way home from school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whether I was alone or with another kid didn't matter much.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there would be 10 or 12 or 14 surrounding us.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
